               <h1>GPA Calculator</h1>
              =20
               <h2>LSU Quality Points and Determining Deficit</h2>
              =20
               <p>Grade Point Average (GPA) is a numerical assessment of a =
student's academic progress.
                  At LSU, GPA is calculated by dividing the total number of=
 quality points earned by
                  the number of hours attempted.</p>
              =20
               <h2>Information on LSU's Plus/Minus Grades and Pass/No Credi=
t Grades</h2>
              =20
               <p>Get the official facts on the <a href=3D"https://www.lsu.=
edu/registrar/grade-policy/plus-minus-grades.php" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"=
noopener">plus/minus grading policy</a> from The Office of the University R=
egistrar, including the plus/minus scale, definitions
                  for letter grades, and frequently asked questions.</p>
              =20
               <p>Do not enter any courses for which a letter grade is not =
assigned. For example: Credit/No
                  Credit, Pass/No Credit, Successful/Unsuccessful.</p>
              =20
               <h2>To use the GPA Calculator</h2>
              =20
               <p>Please refer to your College Record for accurate academic=
 information. For help finding
                  your College Record, see the <a href=3D"https://grok.lsu.=
edu/article.aspx?articleid=3D16482" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">GROK=
 Article on College Record</a>. See our mock <a href=3D"https://www.lsu.edu=
/cas/files/gpacalcpdf.pdf" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">College Recor=
d example</a> for assistance in filling out your GPA calculator.</p>
              =20
               <ul>
                 =20
                  <li>Enter in your Prior Number of Hours (highlighted in b=
lue on our <a href=3D"https://www.lsu.edu/cas/files/gpacalcpdf.pdf" target=
=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">College Record example</a>) and your Prior Qua=
lity Points (highlighted in green). First-semester freshmen do
                     not need to fill out Prior Number of Hours or Prior Qu=
ality Points.</li>
                 =20
                  <li>Enter your course name (optional), hours, and course =
grade for the desired semester
                     (highlighted in yellow).</li>
                 =20
                  <li>Select =E2=80=9CCalculate GPA=E2=80=9D to generate Qu=
ality Points and GPA information.</li>
                  </ul>
              =20
               <h3>*TOPS GPA Disclaimer</h3>
              =20
               <p>TOPS GPA calculation is provided as a courtesy and does n=
ot guarantee TOPS or any
                  other qualification, only the Louisiana Office of Student=
 Financial Assistance (LOSFA)
                  may determine the TOPS award. Visit&nbsp;LOSFA&nbsp;for m=
ore information. TOPS and other educational
                  institutions may use 4, 3, 2, 1, 0 only to calculate GPA.=
</p>
              =20
